Question: Katelyn, a managing partner at a law firm, wants to delegate tasks to Pedro, a legal secretary, in a way that will help him develop.

Which actions would contribute to Pedro's development?
Instruction: Choose all options that best answer the question. 

Katelyn gives Pedro ownership of three tasks that he's been easily performing since joining the firm

Each time Pedro successfully completes a task, Katelyn assigns a new one with added responsibility

Katelyn asks Pedro to take on a relatively difficult task that he hasn't done before, but that she feels would interest him

Katelyn assesses Pedro's skill set and assigns tasks that she feels would expand his skills

Katelyn assigns a series of interesting and important tasks to Pedro, first ensuring there are no risks
